WEBVTT

00:05.438 --> 00:06.872
(THUNDER BOOMING)

00:06.874 --> 00:08.941
<i>♪</i>

00:21.721 --> 00:24.156
(SCREAMING)

00:24.158 --> 00:25.858
<i>♪</i>

00:40.774 --> 00:44.643
DR. GILLMAN:
<i>Humans! The most dangerous</i>
<i>creatures on Earth!</i>

00:44.645 --> 00:45.978
<i>They mock us!</i>

00:45.980 --> 00:47.179
(GROWLING)

00:47.181 --> 00:49.448
<i>They disembowel us!</i>

00:49.450 --> 00:51.550
They eat us!

00:51.552 --> 00:52.484
(GASPING)

00:52.486 --> 00:55.421
Come on,
humans don't eat us.

00:55.423 --> 00:59.224
You saw the movie, Mavis.
Movies don't lie.

00:59.226 --> 01:01.760
I'm going to
need a volunteer.

01:03.363 --> 01:06.298
How does that
always happen?

01:06.833 --> 01:09.068
Now, young lady...

01:09.070 --> 01:09.802
Huh?

01:09.804 --> 01:11.303
Suppose you have
the terrible,

01:11.305 --> 01:16.875
terrible luck of happening
upon a human teenager...

01:18.478 --> 01:19.845
What do you do?

01:19.847 --> 01:22.081
Well, I guess I'd try...

01:22.083 --> 01:23.982
Booga-booga-booga!

01:23.984 --> 01:25.551
Funny, Hank!
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:25.553 --> 01:26.418
All right!

01:26.420 --> 01:29.455
Yes, but will
booga-booga work

01:29.457 --> 01:32.257
against their
superhuman strength!

01:34.727 --> 01:36.195
You see? Science!

01:36.197 --> 01:41.600
And remember, should you ever
encounter a human, beware.

01:41.602 --> 01:43.836
Beware! Beware!

01:43.838 --> 01:46.305
(VOICE DISTORTED)
<i>Beware! Beware! Beware!</i>

01:46.307 --> 01:48.474
Got a sound board for my...

01:48.476 --> 01:51.543
<i>♪ Birthday</i>

01:53.179 --> 01:54.246
(LAUGHING)

01:54.248 --> 01:56.582
That was scarier than
the time I saw Pedro

01:56.584 --> 01:58.617
putting scream cheese
in his armpits.

01:58.619 --> 02:01.753
(LAUGHING) Yeah,
that was kinda weird...

02:01.755 --> 02:02.921
wait, you saw that?

02:02.923 --> 02:05.557
Relax. You can't
listen to Dr. Gillman.

02:05.559 --> 02:09.127
Humans are like ghosts.
They're more afraid of us.

02:09.130 --> 02:10.262
(SCREAMING)

02:10.264 --> 02:13.365
I dunno. They did some
unspeakable things

02:13.367 --> 02:15.501
to that poor pumpkin.

02:16.836 --> 02:18.837
Okay,
I'll prove it to you.

02:18.839 --> 02:21.473
And how are
you gonna do that?

02:22.442 --> 02:24.076
ALL: Oh...

02:24.344 --> 02:26.011
Seriously, how?

02:31.951 --> 02:33.852
I can't watch!

02:35.355 --> 02:37.890
(HIGH-PITCHED XYLOPHONE
NOISES SOUNDING)

02:37.892 --> 02:39.558
Will you stop that?

02:39.560 --> 02:42.327
Sorry.
It's just so awesome.

02:42.329 --> 02:44.830
I'm done.
Promise.

02:44.832 --> 02:46.832
(FLATULENCE NOISES)

02:47.667 --> 02:48.767
Right. Got it.

02:48.769 --> 02:50.402
(COW LOWING)
Can't help myself!

02:50.404 --> 02:52.271
(KLAXON AND
STEAM HORN SOUNDING)

02:52.273 --> 02:53.138
Whoops! My bad!

02:53.140 --> 02:55.641
You can do this.
Nothing to be afraid of.

02:55.643 --> 02:57.309
What's the worst
that can happen?

02:57.311 --> 02:59.411
(GROWLING)

02:59.413 --> 03:02.548
Ah! Okay, what's the second
worst that can happen?

03:02.550 --> 03:04.650
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

03:04.652 --> 03:07.352
(DOORBELL RINGING)

03:07.354 --> 03:09.521
WOMAN: Oh good,
you're early!

03:09.523 --> 03:11.056
We're in a rush!

03:11.058 --> 03:12.057
She's a goner.

03:12.059 --> 03:14.493
Dibs on her stuff.
Rats...

03:14.495 --> 03:17.896
Donald!
The babysitter's here!

03:17.898 --> 03:20.365
DONALD:
Okay! Ready in a jiff!

03:20.367 --> 03:22.034
Babysitter?

03:23.436 --> 03:26.238
Wow.
The future is now.

03:26.240 --> 03:28.440
(KNOCKING)

03:32.011 --> 03:33.645
You're still undead!

03:33.647 --> 03:36.381
Unless you're a human
in a Mavis costume!

03:36.383 --> 03:38.083
Show yourself, imposter!

03:38.085 --> 03:38.817
Hey.

03:38.819 --> 03:41.086
I'm not only undead,
I'm inside!

03:41.088 --> 03:43.155
Nobody ever invites
vampires inside.

03:43.157 --> 03:45.224
This is so awesome!
(WOMAN LAUGHING)

03:45.226 --> 03:47.793
They're coming back! Hide!

03:47.795 --> 03:49.494
What're you doing?

03:49.496 --> 03:52.364
I dunno! I panicked!
Why'd you do it?

03:52.366 --> 03:54.499
I was following you!

03:54.501 --> 03:56.735
I just like to jump.

03:56.869 --> 04:01.106
Okay, the baby's
already asleep.

04:01.108 --> 04:03.775
Oh, isn't she adorable?

04:03.777 --> 04:04.776
(SNORING)

04:04.778 --> 04:07.346
So, you know, there's
really not much to do.

04:07.348 --> 04:08.714
'Cept read our diaries

04:08.716 --> 04:11.883
and eat the emergency
marshmallow reserves.

04:11.885 --> 04:13.252
(LAUGHING NERVOUSLY)

04:13.254 --> 04:14.186
Ignore him.

04:14.188 --> 04:17.089
If you're bored, you can
always read my best seller.

04:17.091 --> 04:19.156
MAVIS: <i>"Monsters Are Not</i>
<i>Your Friends"?</i>

04:19.159 --> 04:22.361
You never can be too careful
with those creatures

04:22.363 --> 04:24.529
across the way.

04:25.398 --> 04:26.732
(GULPING)

04:26.734 --> 04:29.134
(BEEPING)

04:29.136 --> 04:32.070
FEMALE VOICE:
<i>Security enabled.</i>

04:32.072 --> 04:34.506
And whatever you do...

04:34.508 --> 04:39.711
do not open the
door for anyone!

04:39.713 --> 04:42.180
(NERVOUSLY) Uh, sure?

04:42.649 --> 04:44.983
Have fun!

04:47.253 --> 04:49.288
That thing is amazing!

04:49.290 --> 04:50.922
My turn, my turn!

04:50.924 --> 04:52.691
Wendy, don't!

04:54.160 --> 04:55.494
(BEEPING)

04:55.496 --> 04:57.829
(CLANGING)
(CHIRPING)

04:57.997 --> 04:59.631
(HIGH-PITCHED SCREAMING)

04:59.633 --> 05:01.533
I think he took
that pretty well.

05:01.535 --> 05:04.436
So, we're alone
in a human house.

05:04.438 --> 05:05.304
And now what?

05:05.306 --> 05:09.374
You heard the lady.
Time for some babysitting!

05:09.376 --> 05:10.642
(SNORING)

05:10.644 --> 05:13.745
I... have a better idea.

05:13.747 --> 05:15.414
<i>Uno, dos, tres, cuatro!</i>

05:15.416 --> 05:17.249
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

05:17.251 --> 05:18.984
<i>♪ All alone in a human house</i>

05:18.986 --> 05:22.020
<i>♪ Ain't no monster</i>
<i>that's as quiet as a mouse!</i>

05:22.022 --> 05:24.089
<i>♪ All alone in a human house</i>

05:24.091 --> 05:28.193
<i>♪ Hey, check it out,</i>
<i>Hank found a blouse!</i>

05:28.195 --> 05:29.628
(HOWLING)

05:29.630 --> 05:31.697
<i>♪ Hu-man house!</i>
<i>Hu-man house!</i>

05:31.699 --> 05:34.299
<i>♪ We're all alone</i>
<i>in a hu-man house!</i>

05:34.301 --> 05:35.967
<i>♪ Hu-man house!</i>
<i>Hu-man house!</i>

05:35.969 --> 05:39.838
<i>♪ We're all alone</i>
<i>in a hu-man house! ♪</i>

05:39.840 --> 05:41.707
(BARKING AND HOWLING)

05:46.979 --> 05:49.047
<i>♪</i>

05:54.387 --> 05:56.588
HANK:
Fire, fire, fire!

05:57.090 --> 06:00.492
Make it stop!

06:00.494 --> 06:01.626
(TOILET FLUSHING)

06:01.628 --> 06:03.795
You guys, they've got a
Wendy-sized

06:03.797 --> 06:05.764
swimming pool in there!

06:05.766 --> 06:08.233
And sushi!

06:09.102 --> 06:12.037
I would just like to
point out how much fun we had

06:12.039 --> 06:14.673
and how not scary
humans are.

06:14.675 --> 06:16.742
Just like I said.

06:17.944 --> 06:18.610
Trust me.

06:18.612 --> 06:22.280
There is absolutely,
positively, nothing to be
scared of.

06:22.282 --> 06:23.548
(LOUD BANGING)

06:23.550 --> 06:25.083
(LOUD BANGING)

06:25.085 --> 06:27.619
Really set
myself up for that.

06:27.621 --> 06:31.990
Ugh!
Paranoid Mrs. Cartwright,
um, lock me out?

06:31.992 --> 06:35.460
Like I want your kid wiping
boogers on me anyway.

06:35.462 --> 06:36.628
(PHONE RINGING)

06:36.630 --> 06:38.430
(PHONE RINGING)

06:38.865 --> 06:40.031
Hello?

06:40.033 --> 06:41.800
<i>Uh, yeah it's Zoe.</i>

06:41.802 --> 06:44.369
<i>Your crazy security</i>
<i>is on again.</i>

06:44.371 --> 06:46.104
<i>I can't get inside.</i>

06:46.106 --> 06:48.673
But, I already let you in.

06:48.675 --> 06:51.743
Duh, no.
There's some interloper

06:51.745 --> 06:52.944
trying to steal my job.

06:52.946 --> 06:57.449
I'm throwin' serious
shade her way,
but it's not working.

06:57.451 --> 06:59.317
Other baby sitter?

06:59.319 --> 07:01.219
Yeah, and also,

07:01.221 --> 07:03.121
ugh, monsters.

07:03.123 --> 07:05.791
(STAMMERING) Monsters?

07:06.526 --> 07:08.026
My baby!

07:09.862 --> 07:11.229
Tuna tartare.

07:11.231 --> 07:14.332
I wonder if I can get
the tartar on the side.

07:14.334 --> 07:17.469
FEMALE VOICE:
<i>Maximum security initiated.</i>

07:17.471 --> 07:19.471
Ah!
What's happening?

07:27.146 --> 07:28.980
(BABY COOING)

07:29.582 --> 07:31.550
The nose picker!

07:31.552 --> 07:32.317
Mama.

07:32.319 --> 07:35.020
(GASPING)
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

07:35.022 --> 07:38.256
Sorry, but the moment was
just begging for it.

07:38.258 --> 07:40.859
Who's the little gargoyle?

07:41.227 --> 07:46.164
And can you believe it?
Like, not even a ride home!

07:46.866 --> 07:48.500
(SCREAMING)

07:48.502 --> 07:50.702
Nice driving, lady!

07:50.937 --> 07:52.938
Mommy's comin'!

07:54.774 --> 07:57.676
There you go.
Wa-wa.

07:57.678 --> 07:59.978
See?
Nothing to be afraid of.

07:59.980 --> 08:00.946
(CRASHING)

08:00.948 --> 08:03.782
You really gotta know
when to quit.

08:13.292 --> 08:14.559
(ALL SCREAMING)

08:14.561 --> 08:17.896
You monsters
don't know who

08:17.898 --> 08:19.764
you're dealing with!

08:21.133 --> 08:22.033
(SCREAMING)

08:22.035 --> 08:24.703
Sorry, sorry!
Please, don't eat us!

08:24.705 --> 08:26.304
(GROWLING)

08:26.306 --> 08:29.741
I can't believe
how wrong I was.
Humans aren't just scary.

08:29.743 --> 08:30.342
They're terrifying!

08:30.344 --> 08:33.211
Uh, how long before
they turn us into
cookies and eat us?

08:33.212 --> 08:37.883
Mavis, I don't wanna be eaten
by a buncha cookie makers!
What do we do?

08:37.885 --> 08:40.385
We fight back, that's what.

08:41.320 --> 08:43.488
That's an umbrella.

08:43.490 --> 08:44.923
I know.

08:44.925 --> 08:49.394
Okay, okay, let's see what
this wolf-puppy can do.

08:49.396 --> 08:50.896
(BEEPING)
Siren?

08:50.898 --> 08:53.331
(ALARM SOUNDING)
(SCREAMING)

08:54.800 --> 08:56.835
Ooh, try water cannon.

09:00.473 --> 09:02.340
Paint balls!

09:05.244 --> 09:06.878
(YELPING)

09:10.182 --> 09:12.250
(SOBBING)

09:13.786 --> 09:16.688
Ejector?
Whaddya think that does?

09:17.557 --> 09:19.257
(SCREAMING)

09:20.760 --> 09:22.427
(CRASHING)

09:25.565 --> 09:28.266
(THUDDING)
It's on the roof!

09:31.470 --> 09:35.006
Oh! Mavis!
It's in the chimney!

09:35.008 --> 09:36.708
(STRAINING)

09:38.344 --> 09:40.879
Where's the chimney
ejector button?

09:40.881 --> 09:42.280
Ah-ha!

09:46.085 --> 09:47.919
(SNIFFING)

09:48.321 --> 09:50.021
(SCREAMING)

09:51.357 --> 09:52.958
(SCREAMING ANGRILY)

09:52.960 --> 09:54.159
(MONSTERS SCREAMING)

09:54.161 --> 09:55.860
PEDRO:
Somebody help us!

09:56.228 --> 09:57.662
Where's my baby?

09:57.664 --> 10:00.966
Open the Door!

10:00.968 --> 10:03.034
We gotta get out of here!

10:03.202 --> 10:05.337
(POWERING DOWN)

10:06.439 --> 10:09.174
Yes!
Nice work, Hank!

10:09.176 --> 10:11.343
Uh, yeah, thanks.

10:13.512 --> 10:15.614
(ANGRY SCREAMING)

10:17.149 --> 10:19.117
(SIREN SOUNDING)

10:22.488 --> 10:24.689
OFFICER:
Freeze, Monster!

10:25.524 --> 10:26.658
No!

10:26.660 --> 10:28.293
(GIGGLING)

10:33.299 --> 10:34.733
Shh...

10:34.834 --> 10:36.468
(GIGGLING)

10:36.470 --> 10:40.739
I am not a monster!

10:40.741 --> 10:43.174
We'll take it from here,
young lady. Good job.

10:43.176 --> 10:46.277
Just, um, another human doing
human things

10:46.279 --> 10:49.514
like, ah,
any ol' human would.

10:51.617 --> 10:54.019
See?
What'd I tell you guys.

10:54.021 --> 10:57.922
Humans are nothing
to be afraid of.

10:58.224 --> 11:00.191
Donald!
(SOBBING)

11:02.128 --> 11:04.362
So what're you having, hon?

11:04.364 --> 11:05.897
Kitty?
Kitty bird?

11:05.899 --> 11:08.500
(MARIACHI MUSIC PLAYING)

11:10.603 --> 11:14.773
What? We go where
the gigs are, man.

11:15.574 --> 11:18.209
(MARIACHI MUSIC PLAYING)

11:27.553 --> 11:30.088
Time for some Phlegm Ball.

11:30.090 --> 11:32.023
(NECK CRACKING)

11:33.426 --> 11:34.592
(GROWLING)

11:34.594 --> 11:36.828
Neck cracking sound!

11:36.996 --> 11:38.263
(GROWLING)

11:38.265 --> 11:40.098
(BOTH GROWLING)

11:40.100 --> 11:42.467
(NOISE MAKER SOUNDING)

11:43.035 --> 11:45.203
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

11:49.775 --> 11:51.042
Yay!

11:53.446 --> 11:54.879
(SCREAMING)

11:54.881 --> 11:57.949
All right!
Fight the good fight,
Mavis!

11:57.951 --> 11:59.284
<i>♪ Phlegm ball!</i>

11:59.286 --> 12:00.185
<i>♪ That's the name of the game</i>

12:00.187 --> 12:02.854
<i>♪ Bigfoot horks a loogie</i>
<i>and the ball's in play</i>

12:02.856 --> 12:04.823
<i>♪ Chase it,</i>
<i>hustle after that gob</i>

12:04.825 --> 12:07.358
<i>♪ It's slimy, it's drippy,</i>
<i>booger as big as a dog</i>

12:07.360 --> 12:09.861
<i>♪ Spook it, you gotta scare</i>
<i>that sucka straight</i>

12:09.863 --> 12:11.996
<i>♪ Pick up, drag it back,</i>
<i>slam it in it's home</i>

12:11.998 --> 12:15.800
<i>♪ Time to show them monsters</i>
<i>that they just got owned! ♪</i>

12:16.802 --> 12:18.670
Yes! (GROWLING)

12:18.672 --> 12:23.308
Yeah, I'm just gonna say it...
Phlegm Ball is weird.

12:23.310 --> 12:26.745
Ugh. Vampires are
super gross, dude.

12:28.147 --> 12:29.647
Yeah!

12:29.815 --> 12:32.517
Who's the undisputed
Phlegm Ball champ?

12:32.519 --> 12:34.185
This vampire!

12:35.054 --> 12:40.725
Bravo Mavis,
you truly are a champion...

12:40.727 --> 12:42.127
Not!

12:42.129 --> 12:43.495
(CHUCKLING)

12:43.497 --> 12:47.899
Oh, you're over there.
Turn around, turn around!

12:48.167 --> 12:49.567
Klaus.

12:49.569 --> 12:51.236
Come now, why so glum?

12:51.238 --> 12:53.438
You should be
overcome with joy

12:53.440 --> 12:56.074
to see your favorite
cousin Klaus

12:56.076 --> 12:59.177
straight from the
12th century!

12:59.179 --> 13:00.512
Hi, Klaus!

13:00.514 --> 13:03.782
It's "Klaush!"

13:03.784 --> 13:05.250
Whatever, dude.

13:05.252 --> 13:07.018
Anyhoo, I heard someone

13:07.020 --> 13:09.420
was getting a little
too big for her britches

13:09.422 --> 13:11.956
and needed to be
taught a lesson.

13:11.958 --> 13:14.159
(SNAPPING) Ball!

13:18.764 --> 13:21.366
Ha, as if you can beat me!

13:21.368 --> 13:22.700
I'm undefeated!

13:22.702 --> 13:24.402
Yes, well it is
rather easy to win

13:24.404 --> 13:29.440
when every monster
loses on purpose to
Dracula's daughter.

13:30.376 --> 13:31.009
(GULPING)

13:31.011 --> 13:35.280
Come on, no one is
letting me win! Right?

13:36.448 --> 13:39.083
Wha? You guys too?

13:39.085 --> 13:40.985
It's just easier
to let you win.

13:40.987 --> 13:42.620
You're way
too competitive.

13:42.622 --> 13:44.656
I am not!
Oh, yes you are!

13:44.658 --> 13:48.960
And even if by
some impossible chance
it's true, whatevs!

13:48.962 --> 13:51.362
I can still totally beat you.

13:51.364 --> 13:56.668
Oh, goody, so you'll put up
the golden fangs then?

13:56.836 --> 14:00.004
You want my
Dad's lucky fangs?

14:00.006 --> 14:01.739
They're a family heirloom!

14:01.741 --> 14:05.276
With like ten generations
of spit on them.

14:06.312 --> 14:07.045
No way!

14:07.047 --> 14:09.547
Perhaps you are
too...chicken?

14:09.549 --> 14:10.815
(CLUCKING)

14:10.817 --> 14:11.282
But if you give up,

14:11.284 --> 14:16.254
I suppose I may have
to start my victory
dance a little early.

14:16.622 --> 14:18.189
(MAKING BEAT NOISES)

14:18.191 --> 14:20.191
<i>♪ Booty shaking, booty shaking</i>

14:20.193 --> 14:21.593
(MAKING BEAT NOISES)

14:21.595 --> 14:23.361
<i>♪ Booty in your face! Ah!</i>

14:23.363 --> 14:26.297
Ugh! Stop!
We'll play for the fangs.

14:26.299 --> 14:27.799
I never want to
see that again.

14:27.801 --> 14:29.601
And speaking of
never seeing again,

14:29.603 --> 14:34.772
if I win, you stay put in the
12th century for good.

14:34.874 --> 14:37.108
Ugh. Fine. Deal.

14:37.110 --> 14:39.277
(LAUGHING) Whoa!

14:39.279 --> 14:41.479
Silverfish, behave!

14:41.481 --> 14:42.480
(CLEARING THROAT)

14:42.482 --> 14:46.784
Now, perhaps you would
like to meet my teammate...

14:46.952 --> 14:48.620
Number Two.

14:48.622 --> 14:50.521
(ROARING)

14:50.523 --> 14:53.524
(SNICKERING)
Number Two?

14:53.526 --> 14:55.693
Yes. Obviously,
I am number one

14:55.695 --> 14:58.196
and so, naturally,
this is number two.

14:58.198 --> 15:00.164
I can't ask for
a better Number Two.

15:00.166 --> 15:02.100
My number two is solid.

15:02.102 --> 15:03.968
(ALL LAUGHING)

15:07.940 --> 15:10.174
And good luck beating me
with this one.

15:10.176 --> 15:12.410
She has zero
killer instinct.

15:12.412 --> 15:16.447
(GASPING)
I have no killer instinct?

15:16.449 --> 15:19.150
Then what do you call this?

15:19.418 --> 15:19.951
A ukulele.

15:19.953 --> 15:23.254
Oh, thank you, I have been
wondering for a while.

15:23.256 --> 15:25.690
(UKULELE PLAYING)
(KLAUS LAUGHING)

15:28.460 --> 15:29.494
Y'know Wendy,

15:29.496 --> 15:33.331
what our team really needs
is a great cheerleader.

15:33.333 --> 15:36.701
Uh, someone
to push us to victory!

15:36.703 --> 15:37.101
Oh, I see.

15:37.103 --> 15:39.570
If I didn't know better,
I would think that
you're trying to

15:39.572 --> 15:41.105
show me how much
you respect me

15:41.107 --> 15:43.942
by handing over such
an important job!

15:44.476 --> 15:46.110
Do I get pom poms?

15:46.112 --> 15:47.078
Of course.

15:47.080 --> 15:49.180
Yes! Whoo! Whoopee!

15:49.182 --> 15:51.883
See you at game time,
Big Shot!

15:51.885 --> 15:55.320
It doesn't matter
what you do, Mavis,

15:55.322 --> 15:57.689
Count Dracula's
fangs will be mine!

15:57.691 --> 16:01.759
Me and my Number Two
are going to wipe
the floor with you.

16:01.761 --> 16:03.728
(BOTH LAUGHING)

16:03.963 --> 16:05.930
What? What?
What's so funny?

16:05.932 --> 16:07.999
Come on, tell me,
I love jokes!

16:08.001 --> 16:09.934
(BOTH LAUGHING)

16:10.135 --> 16:11.102
(GROANING)

16:11.104 --> 16:13.638
Now I just need a teammate.

16:13.973 --> 16:17.008
Okay, let's see
what you've got!

16:19.878 --> 16:21.846
(ALL GROANING)

16:24.683 --> 16:26.584
(SPLASHING)

16:27.786 --> 16:31.089
I'm running out of options!
(SIGHING)

16:31.091 --> 16:33.992
How am I supposed
to beat Klaus now?

16:33.994 --> 16:35.994
It's "Klaush."

16:36.762 --> 16:37.862
Aw, yeah!

16:37.864 --> 16:38.363
Relax, Mavis,

16:38.365 --> 16:41.899
we're ready to
save your team
and become famous!

16:41.901 --> 16:44.102
HANK: One day, they'll make
a movie about the brave,

16:44.104 --> 16:47.572
plucky underdogs who have no
chance, but somehow win!

16:47.574 --> 16:50.908
Well, even though you're
probably not very good...

16:50.910 --> 16:51.743
Hey!
So true.

16:51.745 --> 16:54.312
I need a teammate.
Okay, Hank, you're in.

16:54.314 --> 16:55.747
Sorry, Pedro.
Yay!

16:55.749 --> 16:56.981
Booyah!

16:56.983 --> 16:58.216
Oh, you don't need me?

16:58.218 --> 17:02.754
You're so gonna regret this!
That movie's gonna bomb!

17:03.655 --> 17:04.821
Ow!

17:04.824 --> 17:06.057
Ouch! Ow!

17:06.059 --> 17:08.259
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

17:08.926 --> 17:12.497
I always knew
you'd recognize I
was the superior choice.

17:12.499 --> 17:16.534
Sure. Also, I figured you'd
be easier to boss around.

17:16.536 --> 17:18.169
Hey, wait a second...

17:18.171 --> 17:19.103
Shush, shush, shush, shush.

17:19.105 --> 17:22.874
I've got a plan to win,
but you need to do
exactly what I say!

17:22.876 --> 17:24.709
Whatever you want, boss!

17:24.711 --> 17:29.814
<i>Welcome to the Golden Fang</i>
<i>Phlegm Ball Championship!</i>

17:29.816 --> 17:33.084
Go Mavis, go Mavis, go Mavis!

17:33.086 --> 17:34.852
(GROWLING)

17:35.087 --> 17:35.953
(GRUNTING)

17:35.955 --> 17:38.189
<i>Things look pretty</i>
<i>tense down there!</i>

17:38.191 --> 17:40.958
<i>Skip,</i>
<i>give us your thoughts.</i>

17:41.894 --> 17:43.161
<i>Exactly!</i>

17:43.163 --> 17:44.762
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

17:50.569 --> 17:52.203
After her!

17:53.705 --> 17:55.306
Yay!
(ROARING)

17:57.109 --> 17:58.843
(CLUCKING)

18:00.045 --> 18:01.546
Hurry!

18:09.521 --> 18:10.988
Gotcha!

18:11.790 --> 18:13.524
You got this, Mavis.

18:15.094 --> 18:16.761
(LAUGHING)

18:18.831 --> 18:21.833
Stop it! Ugh!
Let me go!

18:22.868 --> 18:24.102
Ah!

18:25.237 --> 18:26.404
Go Hank!

18:26.406 --> 18:27.872
Yes!
I'm doing it!

18:27.874 --> 18:30.541
This is the
greatest feeling!

18:30.909 --> 18:32.610
(SCREAMING)

18:36.515 --> 18:40.785
<i>Boom goes the body parts!</i>
<i>That's gonna leave a mark!</i>

18:40.787 --> 18:42.286
(GROWLING)

18:42.288 --> 18:45.423
<i>That's right, Skip,</i>
<i>it's the Crypt-O-Cola</i>

18:45.425 --> 18:47.558
<i>Bone Crunch of the Night!</i>

18:47.560 --> 18:51.863
<i>Crypt-O-Cola, now with</i>
<i>more embalming fluid!</i>

18:51.997 --> 18:52.864
I can't go on.

18:52.866 --> 18:55.867
It'll take forever
to put me back together.

18:55.869 --> 18:57.635
Hey!

18:57.637 --> 18:58.936
Gotcha!

18:58.938 --> 19:00.838
(GASPING, SCREAMING)

19:00.840 --> 19:02.874
After it, you beast!

19:02.876 --> 19:06.010
Ugh! I need a new
teammate, like now!

19:06.012 --> 19:10.014
Ba-kow! I knew you'd come
crawling back bay-bay!

19:10.016 --> 19:11.782
I was clearly
the better choice.

19:11.784 --> 19:15.019
But this is going to make
my role in the movie

19:15.021 --> 19:16.187
even more epic!

19:16.189 --> 19:19.423
Okay, then let's get
that phlegm!

19:19.591 --> 19:23.628
Ow! I should have stretched!

19:23.630 --> 19:24.929
I'm out!

19:24.931 --> 19:25.830
Tell my story!

19:25.832 --> 19:30.001
<i>Oh, boy,</i>
<i>things don't look</i>
<i>so good for Mavis!</i>

19:30.003 --> 19:32.303
<i>Or you, Skip. Yeesh.</i>

19:32.305 --> 19:35.072
Ugh,
I'll never win, now!

19:35.074 --> 19:36.908
What am I gonna do?

19:36.910 --> 19:38.609
(GROANING)

19:38.611 --> 19:41.045
The blob, Mavis.

19:41.047 --> 19:43.047
Use the blob!

19:43.049 --> 19:45.349
Go, Mavis!
I believe in you!

19:45.351 --> 19:47.552
You make good choices!

19:47.554 --> 19:48.753
Hey!

19:48.755 --> 19:50.154
Trust me!

19:50.156 --> 19:51.689
WENDY: Go team!

19:52.090 --> 19:53.324
Yay!

19:53.326 --> 19:55.626
Trust. Right.

19:55.628 --> 19:58.462
Let's get phlegmy!

19:58.464 --> 20:00.264
Whoo! Whoo!

20:00.266 --> 20:02.533
Sorry for tricking
you off the team, Wendy.

20:02.535 --> 20:05.503
You're the best
teammate I ever had...

20:05.505 --> 20:06.671
Hey!

20:06.673 --> 20:07.838
Harsh, but fair.

20:07.840 --> 20:09.974
It's not the same
without you.

20:09.976 --> 20:11.108
I need you.

20:11.110 --> 20:12.109
Well, I don't know, Mavis.

20:12.111 --> 20:15.379
Like you said,
you tricked me
off the team.

20:15.381 --> 20:16.614
Okay!

20:16.616 --> 20:18.115
I made a mistake.
Please!

20:18.117 --> 20:20.284
I'll give you my bag
of Jett Black's hair.

20:20.986 --> 20:23.487
I'll eat the crusts off
your scabby pie!

20:23.489 --> 20:26.757
I'll take over a week of
squeezing your dads
blob heads?

20:26.992 --> 20:28.859
Ding-ding!
That's the one!

20:28.861 --> 20:30.695
Let's do this!

20:31.730 --> 20:34.398
Slither faster!

20:34.400 --> 20:36.067
Ah!
We gotta stop him!

20:36.069 --> 20:40.004
Klaus wants a killer instinct?
Let's kill 'em with kindness.

20:41.573 --> 20:44.442
It's "Klaush!"

20:44.444 --> 20:46.077
(LAUGHING)

20:50.582 --> 20:52.149
I hope you score!

20:52.151 --> 20:54.785
Look at you,
you're so big and strong!

20:54.787 --> 20:57.455
I bet your parents
read to you at night.

20:57.457 --> 20:59.890
You were clearly
raised well!

20:59.892 --> 21:01.158
(GRUNTING)

21:01.160 --> 21:04.395
Nobody's ever been
nice to you before?

21:04.397 --> 21:08.766
That doesn't seem right.
You have such shiny drool.

21:09.534 --> 21:11.035
Foul! No fair!

21:11.037 --> 21:14.505
Referee, call a foul,
she's playing nice!

21:14.507 --> 21:18.175
Come on, forget the game.
Let's go have a picnic.

21:18.177 --> 21:20.478
Boom-drac-alacka!
Yes!

21:20.480 --> 21:21.946
Wait! Wait, wait, wait, wait.

21:21.948 --> 21:24.548
You still have the ball!
You didn't score!

21:24.550 --> 21:27.018
Ze game is not over!

21:27.286 --> 21:29.186
Got it!
No!

21:31.323 --> 21:33.324
KLAUS: Admit defeat!

21:33.326 --> 21:33.891
Never!

21:33.893 --> 21:37.194
You must!
You know you're going to lose!

21:37.196 --> 21:39.196
MAVIS:
The phlegm ball is mine!

21:39.198 --> 21:43.467
Wow, they've been at it for
like three weeks now.

21:43.469 --> 21:44.669
What's this about again?

21:44.671 --> 21:47.605
Dunno, vampire stuff
or something.

21:47.607 --> 21:49.707
(BOTH STRAINING)

21:56.615 --> 21:58.215
<i>♪ Booty shaking, booty shaking</i>

21:58.217 --> 22:01.485
<i>♪ Booty in your face!</i>
<i>Ah! Oh...</i>

22:02.688 --> 22:04.388
<i>♪</i>
